\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Length: 600-800 words. Narrative memo format.
\f0\b0 \
This is the context section \'97 written as fluid, opinionated prose (not bullet points or tables). The reader should come away understanding the company well enough to have an informed conversation about it.\
Cover the following, woven into a coherent narrative (not as discrete subsections):\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What this company is and how it makes money.
\f0\b0  Revenue by segment with actual numbers or well-sourced estimates. Physical operations \'97 facility counts, geographies, scale. Don't just describe the business model; decompose it. Same-store vs. acquisition-driven growth, with the math shown. Revenue quality: recurring vs. non-recurring, customer/payer concentration, contract durability.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Who owns it and what that means for a deal.
\f0\b0  Ownership structure, capital structure, any visible transaction signals. For PE-backed: fund vintage, hold period, co-investors. For public: trading dynamics, activist interest, insider activity, short interest.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What's changed in the last 12 months that matters.
